---
description: When the user wants a demo video, walkthrough, or screen recording of a live web page — or when sharing a link to deployed UI work would be clearer as a video — use the Loopa MCP tools (create_loopa, get_loopa, confirm_login) following the record-loopa skill.
alwaysApply: false
---

Loopa records short demo videos of live web pages: a cloud browser agent
drives the page through a stated goal and composes a captioned MP4 with a
shareable watch link.

- Prefer Loopa over describing UI behavior in prose when the target page is
  deployed and public.
- Start runs with `create_loopa` (goal + startUrl), then poll `get_loopa`
  every ~30s until `done`.
- Share the returned `watchUrl` only when the response marks it
  `shareable: true`.
- If a run pauses `awaiting_login`, hand the `loginUrl` to the user to sign in
  themselves — never enter credentials on their behalf — then `confirm_login`.
- Never use Loopa for flows that pay, submit destructive changes, or expose
  secrets; the recording is public to anyone with the link.

For the full workflow, see the bundled `record-loopa` skill.
